{{Infobox journal | italic title = force | title = Discrete Mathematics & Theoretical Computer Science | cover = | editor = Jens Gustedt | discipline = [[Mathematics]], [[computer science]] | former_names = | abbreviation = Discrete Math. Theor. Comput. Sci. | publisher = | country = | frequency = Quarterly | history = 1997&ndash;present | openaccess = Yes | license = | impact = 0.465 | impact-year = 2011 | website = http://www.dmtcs.org/dmtcs-ojs/index.php/dmtcs | link1 = http://www.dmtcs.org/dmtcs-ojs/index.php/dmtcs/issue/current | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://www.dmtcs.org/dmtcs-ojs/index.php/dmtcs/issue/archive | link2-name = Online archive | JSTOR = | OCLC = 300813040 | LCCN = 98641679 | CODEN = DTCSFX | ISSN = 1462-7264 | eISSN = 1365-8050 }} '''''Discrete Mathematics & Theoretical Computer Science''''' is a [[peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[open access]] [[scientific journal]] covering [[discrete mathematics]] and [[theoretical computer science]]. It was established in 1997 by Daniel Krob ([[Paris Diderot University]]). Since 2001, the [[editor-in-chief]] is Jens Gustedt ([[Institut National de Recherche en Informatique et en Automatique]]).
== Abstracting and indexing == The journal is abstracted and indexed in ''[[Mathematical Reviews]]'' and the [[Science Citation Index Expanded]]. According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', the journal has a 2011 [[impact factor]] of 0.465.<ref name=WoS>{{cite book |year=2013 |chapter=Discrete Mathematics & Theoretical Computer Science |title=2011 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Science |accessdate=2013-01-28 |series=[[Web of Science]] |postscript=.}}</ref>
