{{Infobox recurring event | name = <!--Uses page name if omitted--> | native_name = | logo = | logo_caption = | image = | imagesize = | caption = | date = | begins = <!--2018 date {{start date|2018|09|08}} --> | ends = <!--2018 date {{end date|2018|09|12}} --> | prev = ISMB/ECCB 2017 | next = ECCB 2018 | frequency = Annually | location = [[Athens]], [[Greece]] (2018) | years_active = {{age|2002|10|06}} | first = | last = | participants = | attendance = 1,500 | genre = | budget = | patron = | organised = <!--"organized=" also works--> Artemis Hatzigeorgiou, Pantelis Bagos (2018&nbsp;chairs) | people = | website = {{URL|http://eccb18.org}} | footnotes = }}
[[File:Janet Thornton giving a talk at the European Conference on Computational Biology 2012 in Basel.jpeg|thumb|[[Janet Thornton]] at the [[UniProt]] symposium, a satellite event to ECCB 2012 in [[Basel]], giving a talk on [[molecular evolution]].]]
The '''European Conference on Computational Biology''' ('''ECCB''') is a [[scientific meeting]] on the subjects of [[bioinformatics]] and [[computational biology]]. It covers a wide spectrum of disciplines, including bioinformatics, computational biology, [[genomics]], computational [[structural biology]], and [[systems biology]]. ECCB is organized annually in different European cities. Since 2007, the conference has been held jointly with [[Intelligent Systems for Molecular Biology]] (ISMB) every second year. The conference also hosts the European [[International Society for Computational Biology|ISCB]] Student Council Symposium.<ref name=ESCS>{{cite web |url=http://escs.iscbsc.org/ |title=Homepage |last1= |first1= |last2= |first2= |website= |publisher=European Student Council Symposium |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6AXucS60V?url=http://escs.iscbsc.org/ |archivedate=September 9, 2012 |accessdate=September 8, 2012 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Abeel | first1 = T. | last2 = De Ridder | first2 = J. | last3 = Peixoto | first3 = L. | title = Highlights from the 5th International Society for Computational Biology Student Council Symposium at the 17th Annual International Conference on Intelligent Systems for Molecular Biology and the 8th European Conference on Computational Biology | doi = 10.1186/1471-2105-10-S13-I1 | journal = BMC Bioinformatics | volume = 10 | pages = I1 | year = 2009 | pmid = 19840405 | pmc =2764124 }}</ref> The proceedings of the conference are published by the journal ''[[Bioinformatics (journal)|Bioinformatics]]''.
==History== ===Formation=== ECCB was formed with the intent of providing a European conference focusing on advances in computational biology and their application to problems in molecular biology. The conference was initially to be held on a rotating basis, with the idea that previously successful regional conferences (for instance, the German Conference on Bioinformatics (GCB), the French Journées Ouvertes Biologie, Informatique et Mathématiques (JOBIM) conference and the British Genes, Proteins & Computers (GPC) conference) would be jointly held with ECCB if that region was hosting ECCB in that particular year.<ref name=2002-editorial>{{cite journal|last=Lengauer|first=T.|title=Editorial|journal=Bioinformatics|date=1 April 2002|volume=18|issue=Suppl 2|pages=S1|doi=10.1093/bioinformatics/18.suppl_2.S1}}</ref><ref name=2003-editorial>{{cite journal|last=Lenhof|first=H.-P.|author2=Sagot, M.-F.|title=ECCB 2003|journal=Bioinformatics|date=8 October 2003|volume=19|issue=Suppl 2|pages=ii1–ii2|doi=10.1093/bioinformatics/btg1051}}</ref> The first ECCB conference was held in October 2002 in [[Saarbrücken]], [[Germany]] and was chaired by [[Hans-Peter Lenhof]].<ref name=2002-organisation>{{cite journal|title=ECCB 2002 Organization|journal=Bioinformatics|date=1 April 2002|volume=18|issue=Suppl 2|pages=S2–S3|doi=10.1093/bioinformatics/18.suppl_2.S2}}</ref> 69 scientific papers were submitted to the conference.<ref name=2002-editorial />
===Partnership with ISMB=== In 2004, ECCB was jointly held with the [[Intelligent Systems for Molecular Biology]] (ISMB) conference for the first time. It was also co-located with the Genes, Proteins & Computers conference. This meeting, held in [[Glasgow]], [[UK]], was the largest [[bioinformatics]] conference ever held,<ref name=iscb-history>{{cite web|title=History of ISCB|url=http://www.iscb.org/iscb-history|work=www.iscb.org|accessdate=19 September 2013}}</ref> attended by 2,136 delegates, submitting 496 scientific papers.<ref name=ismbeccb2004>{{cite web|title=ISMB/ECCB 2004|url=http://www.iscb.org/cms_addon/conferences/ismbeccb2004/|accessdate=19 September 2013}}</ref> [[International Society for Computational Biology|ISCB]] Board member and Director of the [[Spanish National Bioinformatics Institute]] [[Alfonso Valencia]] considers ISMB/ECCB 2004 to be an important milestone in the history of ISMB: "it was the first one where the balance between Europe and the States became an important part of the conference. It was here that we established the rules and the ways and the spirit of collaboration between the Americans and the Europeans."<ref name="Gibson2012">{{cite journal|last=Gibson|first=Todd A.|title=The Roots of Bioinformatics in ISMB|journal=PLoS Computational Biology|volume=8|issue=8|pages=e1002679|doi=10.1371/journal.pcbi.1002679|pmid=22952443|pmc=3431341|year=2012}}</ref> The success of the joint conference paved the way for future European ISMB meetings to be held jointly with ECCB. In January 2007, ISMB and ECCB agreed to hold joint conferences in Europe every other year, beginning with ISMB/ECCB 2007.<ref name="Linial2008">{{Cite journal | last1 = Linial | first1 = M. | last2 = Mesirov | first2 = J. P. | last3 = Morrison Mckay | first3 = B. J. | last4 = Rost | first4 = B. | title = ISMB 2008 Toronto | doi = 10.1371/journal.pcbi.1000094 | journal = PLoS Computational Biology | volume = 4 | issue = 6 | pages = e1000094 | year = 2008 | pmid = 18584023| pmc =2427177 }}</ref> This pattern has been confirmed to continue until at least 2017.<ref name=iscb-newsletter-17-2>{{cite web|title=ISCB Newsletter - Summer 2014 - Volume 17, Issue 2|url=http://www.iscb.org/images/stories/newsletter/newsletter17-2/ISCB-newsletter-17-2-FINAL.pdf|publisher=ISCB|accessdate=8 August 2014}}</ref>
