yana Shaposhnikova |last7 = Sobolevskii |first7 = P.|last8 = Solomiak |first8 = M.|title = Mathemathical Work of Vladimir Maz'ya (on the occasion of his 60th birthday) |journal = Functional Differential Equations |volume = 4 |issue = 1–2 |pages = 3–11 |year = 1997 |url = http://www.mai.liu.se/~vlmaz/60birthday/60birthday.html|mr = 1491785 |zbl = 0896.35002 }}</ref> * [[Naum Meiman]] (1912–2001), complex analysis, partial differential equations, and mathematical physics<ref>{{cite book | last = Paul | first = Lisa | title = Swimming in the Daylight: An American Student, a Soviet-Jewish Dissident, and the Gift of Hope |url = http://www.goodreads.com/book/show/10295308-swimming-in-the-daylight| publisher = Skyhorse Publishing | series = | year = 2011 | doi = | isbn = 978-1-61608-203-1}}</ref> * [[Nathan Mendelsohn]] (1917–2006), discrete mathematics<ref>{{cite news|first=Ron|last=Csillag|url=http://umanitoba.ca/science/Mendelsohn-Prize/Nathan-obituary.pdf|title=Nathan Mendelsohn, Scholar 1917–2006|newspaper=[[The Globe and Mail]]|date=July 21, 2006}}</ref> * [[Karl Menger]] (1902–1985), mathematician{{Sfnm|1a1=O'Connor|1a2=Robertson|1loc=[http://www-history.mcs.st-andrews.ac.uk/Biographies/Menger.html Karl Menger]}} * [[Abraham Joseph Menz]] (18th century), mathematician and rabbi<ref>{{Cite Jewish Encyclopedia|url=http://www.jewishencyclopedia.com/articles/10688-menz-abraham-joseph-ben-simon-wolf|title=Menz, Abraham Joseph ben Simon Wolf|first1=Gotthard|last1=Deutsch|first2=S. J.|last2=Levinson}}</ref> * [[Yves Meyer]] (born 1939), mathematician; Abel Prize (2017)<ref>{{cite news |last=Hoffman|first=Daniel|date=March 22, 2017|title=French Jewish Mathematician Wins ‘Math Nobel’|url=http://forward.com/fast-forward/366827/french-jewish-mathematician-wins-math-nobel/|work=[[The Forward]]}}</ref> * [[Ernest Michael]] (1925–2013), general topology<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.legacy.com/obituaries/seattletimes/obituary.aspx?pid=164555671|title=Obituary: Ernest Arthur Mich