ss | asin=B01DUEBQSC|page=1}}</ref><ref name=james/> * [[Edouard Zeckendorf]] (1901–1983), number theory<ref>{{cite journal|first=Clark|last=Kimberling|author-link=Clark Kimberling|title=Edouard Zeckendorf|journal=Fibonacci Quarterly|volume=36|number=5|year=1998|pages=416–418|url=https://www.fq.math.ca/Scanned/36-5/kimberling.pdf}}</ref> * [[Doron Zeilberger]] (born 1950), combinatorics<ref name=jinfo/> * [[Efim Zelmanov]] (born 1955), mathematician; Fields Medal (1994)<ref name=jinfofields/> * [[Tamar Ziegler]] (born 1971), ergodic theory and arithmetic combinatorics; Erdős Prize (2011) * [[Leo Zippin]] (1905–1995), solved Hilbert's fifth problem{{Sfnm|1a1=O'Connor|1a2=Robertson|1loc=[http://www-history.mcs.st-andrews.ac.uk/Biographies/Zippin.html Leo Zippin]}} * [[Abraham Ziv]] (1940–2013), number theory * [[Benedict Zuckermann]] (1818–1891), mathematician and historian{{r|EJ|p=V21:678}} * [[Moses Zuriel]] (16th century), mathematician<ref>{{Cite Jewish Encyclopedia|title=Zuriel, Moses ben Samuel|url=http://www.jewishencyclopedia.com/articles/15303-zuriel-moses-ben-samuel|first=M.|last=Seligsohn}}</ref>
